<h3>The Trade-off: Discovery vs. Enrichment</h3>
<p><strong>Capture limitations:</strong>
- Only enriches sequences similar to probes
- Truly novel organisms (no close relative in design) will be missed
- ~15-20% sequence divergence is typical capture limit</p>
<p><strong>Mitigation strategies:</strong>
1. Include diverse representatives of each genus
2. Use degenerate probe designs for variable regions
3. Run a subset of samples with shotgun (no capture) for discovery
4. Iteratively update probe design as you find new taxa</p>
<h3>Recommended Workflow for FRESH</h3>
<pre><code>┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                    │
│   Phase 1: Discovery + Probe Design                                │
│   ├── Deep shotgun metagenomics on 50 diverse samples             │
│   │   (accept the host contamination cost for discovery)          │
