<td>Polyamine pathway; complements speA/ldcC</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>prtS</strong></td>
<td>Prevotella proteases</td>
<td>Tissue degradation; P. bivia in your HIV+ samples</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2>The Innovation Layer</h2>
<p>Here's where your lab differentiates:</p>
<h3>1. UMI-Tagged Amplicons for Strain Deconvolution</h3>
<pre><code>Standard amplicon workflow:
  Sample → PCR → Sequence → ASVs → Can't resolve strain mixtures

UMI workflow:
  Sample → PCR with UMI primers → Sequence → Group by UMI → Consensus per molecule
         ↓
  True molecule counting (absolute)
  Strain mixture deconvolution
  PCR chimera elimination
  PCR bias correction
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Apply to:</strong> cpn60, rpoB (your strain-resolution amplicons)</p>
<p><strong>Innovation:</strong> Nobody has done UMI-tagged cpn60 for vaginal microbiome. This is publishable methods work.</p>
<h3>2. Multi-Marker Taxonomic Integration</h3>
<pre><code>Current state of field:
  16S → taxonomy
  Done.

Your innovation:
  16S V4    ─┐
  16S V1-V3 ─┼─→ Concordance analysis ─→ Confidence-weighted taxonomy
  cpn60     ─┤                         ─→ Novel taxa flagging
  rpoB      ─┘                         ─→ Database gap identification
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Informatics development:</strong>
- Concordance scoring: Do all markers agree? If not, why?
- Weighted consensus: Trust cpn60 for Gardnerella, V1-V3 for Lactobacillus
- Discordance flagging: Samples where markers disagree get prioritized for your collaborator's metagenomics</p>
<h3>3. Functional Scoring from Amplicons</h3>
<p>This is the killer innovation. Instead of metagenomics for functional inference, you directly measure:</p>
<pre><code>Inflammation Potential Score = f(nanH, vly, speA, ldcC, hdc)

Protection Score = f(ldhD, total_Lactobacillus, L.crispatus_abundance)

Risk Index = Inflammation_Score / Protection_Score
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Validation:</strong> Correlate with your Luminex cytokine data, CD4+ T cell counts, and ultimately HIV acquisition.</p>
<p><strong>This becomes a predictive biomarker panel</strong> - clinically translatable, deployable in Durban.</p>
<h3>4. South African Reference Database</h3>
<p>Your culturomics (600 isolates) + amplicon data = population-specific reference</p>
<pre><code>From each isolate:
├── Full 16S (Sanger or long-read)
├── Full cpn60
├── Full rpoB  
├── Functional genes present/absent
└── Phenotypic characterization

Output:
├── FRESH-DB: South African FGT reference
├── Primer validation against local strains
├── Novel taxa documentation
└── Public resource (citable, impactful)
</code></pre>
