<h3>Multiplexing Strategy</h3>
<p>You can dramatically reduce costs by pooling:</p>
<pre><code>Option A: Separate libraries, pooled sequencing
├── More flexible
├── Easier troubleshooting
├── Higher cost

Option B: Multiplexed PCR pools
├── Pool 1: 16S V4 + V1-V3 (same gene, different regions)
├── Pool 2: cpn60 + rpoB (both ~500bp, bacteria-specific)
├── Pool 3: Functional genes (all ~300-500bp)
├── Lower cost
├── Requires careful primer design to avoid cross-reactivity
</code></pre>
